# 🌡️ Temperature Alert System using DHT11 and Arduino

This Arduino project reads temperature using a DHT11 sensor and activates a buzzer alarm when the temperature exceeds a predefined threshold (30°C). It's ideal for basic thermal monitoring applications.

---

## 🧠 Features

- Reads temperature using the **DHT11 sensor**
- Activates a **buzzer** if the temperature > 30°C
- Sends real-time data to **Serial Monitor**
- Compact and beginner-friendly temperature alert logic

---

## 🔌 Circuit Components

| Component | Arduino Pin |
|----------|-------------|
| DHT11    | D2          |
| Buzzer   | D9          |

